OL,6,F"Over the three years we had it, I
OL,7,Fhate to think how much I put in
OL,8,Fthere," she says. "(the Post Office)
OL,9,Fjust threatened you all the time. They
OL,10,Fwere bullies...They bullied us from
OL,11,Fthe day they set foot in our shop."
OL,13,FShe did not face criminal prosecution,
OL,14,Fbut tells us she felt 'scammed and
OL,15,Fbullied' by the Post Office, whom she
OL,16,Fsays bought her business back from her
OL,17,Fat a fraction of the true value.
OL,19,FAfter losing her job, business, and
OL,20,Fher home, Jo's mental health has
OL,21,Fsuffered.
